						<summary>

						<p>Another Nandi pillar set up near the northern <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> out side the Mallikārjuna temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 17th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the name of Parvataya-Nāgaya, son of the mason Māchi Batu of Dēvarakoṇḍa.</p>						

						</summary>
